57
00:02:24,190 --> 00:02:26,270
“That could result in about

58
00:02:26,270 --> 00:02:29,160
40 senior executives being replaced”?!

59
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:32,750
How many senior vice presidents does a company
need?

60
00:02:32,750 --> 00:02:34,340
About 40, I guess.

61
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:37,300
The Chinese Communist Party has plans to put

62
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:41,470
a radio frequency ID chip in cars across China

63
00:02:41,470 --> 00:02:43,910
starting July 1st.

64
00:02:43,910 --> 00:02:45,360
Officials have described it as a way to

65
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:48,160
“help ease worsening traffic congestion...

66
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:51,950
partly because clogged roads contribute to
air pollution.”

67
00:02:51,950 --> 00:02:54,360
Which is why it’s being implemented by...

68
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:56,590
the Ministry of Public Security.

69
00:02:56,590 --> 00:02:59,460
Now while whole chip-tracking-your-car thing

70
00:02:59,460 --> 00:03:01,530
may sound like some scary,

71
00:03:01,530 --> 00:03:03,780
big brother type surveillance plan,

72
00:03:03,780 --> 00:03:05,050
don’t worry!

73
00:03:05,050 --> 00:03:06,320
It’s voluntary.

74
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:07,320
For now.

75
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:08,610
That’ll change on January 1st.

76
00:03:08,610 --> 00:03:12,330
Then it’ll become mandatory for all new
vehicles.

77
00:03:12,330 --> 00:03:14,710
But even without this ID chip program,

78
00:03:14,710 --> 00:03:18,360
the Ministry of Public Security can still
track wherever you go.

79
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:23,330
They’ve got 200 million surveillance cameras
across the China,

80
00:03:23,330 --> 00:03:26,330
and they can already track your car by its
model, color,

81
00:03:26,330 --> 00:03:28,720
and license plate number.

82
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:30,220
Speaking of vehicles,

83
00:03:30,220 --> 00:03:32,930
truck drivers across nine provinces in China

84
00:03:32,930 --> 00:03:34,480
have been protesting.

85
00:03:35,340 --> 00:03:36,960
They’re gathering in parking lots,

86
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:39,010
and even on major highways.

87
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:41,600
The truck drivers complaining about high gas
prices

88
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:43,950
and excessive highway tolls.

89
00:03:43,950 --> 00:03:46,580
But also they’re kind of mad about how they
police

90
00:03:46,580 --> 00:03:48,710
keep harassing them.

91
00:03:48,710 --> 00:03:51,530
“Overthrow the CCP!”

92
00:03:51,530 --> 00:03:53,640
Overthrow the Chinese Communist Party?!

93
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:54,660
Whoa!

94
00:03:54,660 --> 00:03:57,170
People aren’t supposed to think like that!

95
00:03:57,170 --> 00:03:58,170
No!

96
00:03:58,170 --> 00:03:59,510
They’re supposed to be patient

97
00:03:59,510 --> 00:04:02,600
while the Chinese Communist Party fixes all
the problems

98
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:06,690
